    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but isn't it also true that the \"original meaning\" can be really vague or even contradictory depending on which historian you talk to? it seems like there's a lot of debate about whether it's actually a reliable way to interpret the law or if it's just easier to use than more modern approaches.",
